						<summary>

						<p>Stone with sculpture called Komara Rāma.</p>						

						<p>Dēvarāya II A.D. 1430.</p>						

						<p>This inscription dated Śaka year 1352, Sādhārana, Kā[rtika] • • • • • Wednesday, records the death of Jambe-Nāyaka, son of Harige-Nāyaka, in a fight. The hero's two wives Kāmeva-Nāyakiti and Lakava-Nāyakiti also died after him.</p>						

